<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shadowblades</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: Well I don't really need to say anything here, since we all know alot about them from this board.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hunters</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: Kobolts with little bows and big sticks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Their melee can be quite nasty, as can bowshots of course.  They have self buffs as do rangers, and *can* charm pets.  Normally pets arn't used while soloing, but they can be quite nasty.  I don't know if they will run or fight, it really depends on the player I guess.  They generally don't have super high levels of stealth, or so I have read... Spear/bow/beastcraft is too tempting. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Seers<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Healers</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: Caution is needed here, as like all the main healers they get shout targeted/group heals.  Pacifism spec'ed healers have stuns and mezes up the wazoo, and augmentation healers can be nasty hitters.  Alot of healers are disenchanted with Pacifism after the changes, so have moved towards more augmentation or mending...  Again they have the ability to use big 2handed hammers, so they can be tough.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shaman</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: Alot of them are Cave specialized, but I think the class still needs work even with the enhancements.  Their healing aside from the regeneration abilities isn't up to par with the healers.... They lack the heal shouts, and the augmentation abilities of healers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Mystics</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Runemasters</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: Most of them are either spec'ed in either Supression (Bladeturn, Snare DD) or Runecarving (Bolts, ranged AE)... They are the easiest target for a assassin in the midgard realm it seems... Not much else to say of note, except perhaps that they do get a run speed buff.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spiritmasters</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->: Spiritwhat?  Rare as all get out from what I hear.  They may be gaining in popularity with the changes to their pets, adding a range of nasty procs... but still it is a ranger weak RvR class. Watch for them to be using AE debuffs, and until its fixed the pet seeing stealth bug.  They have a PBAE mez shout, which can be rough, but probibly won't pose too much of a threat if you ever find one.<br>
<br>
I hope this information is helpful, but I have no idea what colors, and race is most prevailent for most... Well generally trolls are melee and such, but if others can fill what I have missed/screwed up maybe we can start getting a better idea of their classes. <p>Eldoran Earthsong, Retired Minstrel of E'ci.<BR>
